values:
I'm not better yet. I'm trying to be better, I really am, but my throat is kicking my ass and that's quite a journey so I think it might be stronger than me.&nbsp;

As it turns out, I'm going to be able to go to Adrienne's party, but I'm not going to be able to drink because my life is silly right now, so I'm just going to dress up (maybe...if I'm allowed to go shopping or I can find someone to take me) and probably be the DD for all of my lush friends. I think they'll probably need me. And I'll need their gas money since I no longer work. At all. Ever. Besides, my 21st birthday is rapidly approaching and I'll have plenty of time to catch up on my drinking once that happens.&nbsp;

My problem now is going to be getting all the time off work that I need. I think I've probably hit my quota for like, oh, I don't know... THE YEAR!?! I still need the 20th off and the 26th and 27th off though because I need those days for me and my Lyssa. Her boy is coming in from New York on the 20th and obviously our birthdays will be celebrated on the 26th-28th. Damn you Mom and your having me on Memorial Day weekend! Seriously, what was she thinking?

I'm so damn bored right now. My mom has the day off and I wanted to go out and do something fun (i.e. anything that doesn't include being inside this house) but all she wants to do is clean. I would like to go get a new memory card for my camera because mine's broken or some shit and prom is in a few days. Looks like it's the couch for me... AGAIN.&nbsp;

I hate my life.

I get to see my Alyssa today. She is leaving for Mi-motherfucking-ami and she's in town today so I finally get to see her before she leaves. I miss that girl like crazy. It's going to be so much harder when she lives in New York... I know that's what she's always wanted to do but to tell you the truth, I fucking hate it. She's already too far away as it is.&nbsp;

Last night I was over at Lauren's. It was a pretty low-key night... except that the punkin was sick and I felt so bad for her. I wish they made good medicine for babies that they'd actually take so that they don't have to feel that way. Being sick=no fun.&nbsp;

I've decided that I'm done trying to force things to happen in my love life. I'm just going to see what happens, because truthfully I'm done and I'm tired and I figure that if someone really wants to be with me... they'll make that time and that effort to be a part of my life. Just let the pieces fall and I'll clean them up later.&nbsp;

Eh. I'm just bored I guess. I'm waiting to go to lunch with Lyssa and I'm all pretty right now and this is seriously the best thing that I can think to do.

I think it's time for me to just be happy and content and to deal with it. Every once in a while I get this feeling like I'm going to go back to where I was 8 months ago and I'm going to be happy again... really happy like when we were together. I was really happy then. Now I'm just filling spaces. Am I always going to be filling these spaces with more useless bullshit and these worthless guys that call me and I can convince myself that "this could really be something" and everyone knows it won't be because he's not Matt and I'm just too damn hard to please. Probably. I wonder if I'll ever be over it. Lauren says I will. Normally she would be right, but I can't... no, I won't let this go. I don't want to. I have love, even if it's just one sided and hey, one side is better than none right? Willing my phone to ring is a lot more fun than all the productive things I could fill my time with. I just keep thinking, there has to be a reason. It's been four years and maybe this is the "been through&nbsp;a lot together" phase that everyone talks about on their wedding days. I either don't respect myself at all or I'm a hopeless, hopeless romantic. I'm a mess either way.&nbsp;

I don't do fun anymore. Sarah called me last night at 11:00 because she wanted me to go to a party with her with lots and lots of guys and you know what I told her? I told her that I was tired and that I was going to bed... and you know what? I did. I hope I get more fun after I turn 21. That's what I'm expecting to happen because it's kind of hard to go out and have fun now because I can't go anywhere and drink with friends. So, maybe I'm allowed to be this boring now and then I can be fun when I get a little older. I just don't want to piss away all my hard work now because I think I'm really going to need it soon.&nbsp;

I just got done being sick... AGAIN. No, I'm not even done yet. I'm on an antibiotic for the next two weeks. I finally went to go see a specialist and he said that if I wanted my tonsils out, he'd take them out for me. Recovery is going to be a bitch, but I can't do this shit twice a year for the rest of my life. Especially considering what I'm going to be doing for the rest of my life. Honestly, how many times a day am I going to be exposed to this shit? I'll have strep throat every two weeks. No thank you.&nbsp;

I got the Fall Out Boy tickets last night. Now I'm really going. Because I was just planning on going and now it's here, right in front of my. Three tickets that confirm... yes, you are going. Something to look forward to, finally.
